WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Disinformation during the pandemic

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:05.520
Good morning everybody

00:00:07.100 --> 00:00:12.800
As I said in the previous part, first panel 
opening today´s conference Going Digital

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:20.394
is about disinformations, specifically disinformation
 in the time of global pandemic of Covid-19

00:00:20.594 --> 00:00:26.000
Before introducing guests and discussion,
 let me say few organizational things,

00:00:26.674 --> 00:00:32.000
Whole discussion shall be on 60 minutes 
and shall be dived into 2 main parts.

00:00:32.200 --> 00:00:39.000
In the first part there is discussion
 about 3 main parts, subtopics.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Subtopics regarding disinformatio
n during Covid time.

00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:51.810
And whats is it about? We are going to talk
 about most frequent disinformations,

00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:55.000
information narratives: 
who is spreading them and why?

00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:58.830
How it affects our society and 
political environment.

00:00:59.030 --> 00:01:04.900
And also how to defend
 and is it even possible to defend that?

00:01:05.100 --> 00:01:08.810
In the second part of discussion we are going to
 take a look on viewers questions

00:01:09.010 --> 00:01:14.440
I hereby appeal to you, the audience,
 who are watching us, you can ask questions,

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:23.190
but please be specific of person who you are asking, 
to avoid everyone answering your question.

00:01:23.390 --> 00:01:27.700
I will also ask you to turn off your
 microphones and cameras.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:36.560
Before we start discussion, I would love to introduce
 our panelists who are here today with us.

00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:41.350
In the first place I want to welcome Mr. Jakub Kalensky,
 who is analytist of US think tank, Atlantic Council.

00:01:41.550 --> 00:01:47.470
Specifically he is part of program 
called Digital Forensic Research Lab.

00:01:47.670 --> 00:01:57.620
In the past he also was in EU team´s East StratCom
 Task Force, which was dealing with
 disinformational campaing and hybrid threats

00:01:58.041 --> 00:02:06.481
I also welcome here Marketa Gregorova, 
member of European Parliament of Pirate party,
 also Vice-Chair European Pirate Party,

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:14.671
who deals with hybrid threats, disinformations 
and cyber security in European Parliament.

00:02:14.871 --> 00:02:23.800
Next who I welcome here is Alžběta Bajerová, 
who same as Mr Kalensky, is not physically present here,
 but we can see them on monitors.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.500
Mrs Bajerova is analyst of 
Association for International Affairs.

00:02:27.700 --> 00:02:30.000
She also operates in Brusel, in NATO's HQ,

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:37.390
where she also works as analysist dealing with 
disinformations and influential operations in Transatlantic area.

00:02:37.590 --> 00:02:46.710
At last but not at least I welcome here
 Mr. Zdeněk Strnad, chief editor of Flowee City.

00:02:46.910 --> 00:02:50.900
Welcome here everybody
 and lets move to discussion.

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:56.600
As I said before, at first we will discuss 
the most frequent disinformations

00:02:56.600 --> 00:03:04.820
and disinformative narratives about COVID-19
 we can meet and see on Internet

00:03:06.021 --> 00:03:10.630
and who is spreading them
 and what is their motive?

00:03:10.830 --> 00:03:17.180
At this point I would like to ask Mr. Kalensky
 if he can enlighten us, with his expertise.

00:03:19.380 --> 00:03:27.890
What narratives and disinformatins 
about Covid-19 do you perceive,

00:03:28.090 --> 00:03:32.000
who are the most common disseminators 
and what is their motivation?

00:03:32.200 --> 00:03:39.940
Thank you for invitation, the most common narratives,
 why they are being spread and disserminators.

00:03:40.140 --> 00:03:47.070
That is a thing for hour long talk. 
So I will try to summarize that into 2 minutes.

00:03:48.270 --> 00:03:54.640
The most common narratives will be heading
 to who is responsible for that virus or pandemic,

00:03:54.840 --> 00:04:02.320
is it as serious as official sources claim
 and how to solve it.

00:04:02.520 --> 00:04:06.610
So you will be questioning whole existence of the pandemic,

00:04:06.810 --> 00:04:10.080
you will be questioning creation that in China.

00:04:10.280 --> 00:04:19.950
Instead you will be saying that this brought US Army
 who is responsible for worlwide spreading.

00:04:20.150 --> 00:04:28.940
You will be fabricate nonsenses about organizating that
 by Bill Gates to put microchips in brains via vaccination.

00:04:29.140 --> 00:04:33.180
which we have there already from previous
 pandemics, from different people.

00:04:33.380 --> 00:04:45.590
According those desinformaters you will be spreading
 lies about how to solve this pandemic.

00:04:45.590 --> 00:04:47.590
How to cure this disease.

00:04:47.790 --> 00:04:53.810
The whole thing has just one goal,
 to undermine the West,

00:04:54.010 --> 00:05:00.430
undermine institutions, including solid media,
 governments and their institutions.

00:05:02.631 --> 00:05:06.990
This partly answers to the questions,
 who is spreading that.

00:05:07.190 --> 00:05:18.200
The main informative aggressors are Russia and China.
 They feel to be in coflict with the West.

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:26.320
they want to choose mostly information means,
 not military means

00:05:26.520 --> 00:05:39.150
so they use the information sphere to actually weaken the West
 at all levels at which they are able to do so

00:05:39.350 --> 00:05:49.930
And one of them may be to questioning that
 you have to trust the government, WHO or your doctors

00:05:50.130 --> 00:05:53.610
about how serious it is and how to deal with it.

00:05:53.810 --> 00:06:02.810
Of course, then as the actors here have a strategy
 and they know what they are doing,

00:06:03.010 --> 00:06:09.120
unfortunately, 
it is simply  law of information confrontation,

00:06:09.320 --> 00:06:15.930
rolls a pile of useful idiots in our environment, 
Ilona Csáková or Roman Šmucler,

00:06:16.130 --> 00:06:20.500
but of course you would find them in every the language space, 
someone who will repeat the nonsense

00:06:20.700 --> 00:06:25.400
and they will not know that they serve as 
useful idiots to some information aggressors.

00:06:25.600 --> 00:06:33.390
So thats briefly from me and I would let speak 
other speakers. We can explain details later.

00:06:33.590 --> 00:06:40.600
Thank you, you mentioned several levels of those
 disseminators, from state actors to useful idiots.

00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:47.099
I would now like to ask Mrs Markéta Gregorová
 about the motivation of these disseminators,

00:06:47.299 --> 00:06:54.609
Mr Kalenský also mentioned China as a state actor
 who is actually trying to change the overall narrative,

00:06:54.809 --> 00:07:00.159
that China is not the source of the virus, 
on the contrary, the source of the virus are other countries,

00:07:00.359 --> 00:07:04.919
that China is successful
 in fighting the virus and helps everyone.

00:07:05.119 --> 00:07:10.269
What do you think, has China been successful?

00:07:10.469 --> 00:07:16.200
Successful in this effort to change this narrative
 and what do you actually think about their motivations?

00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:18.600
Why is China doing it?

00:07:18.800 --> 00:07:28.000
Thank you for the question, I'll start with
 those motivations,  because I just think it's important
 to mention that motivations can be different.

00:07:28.200 --> 00:07:34.200
as we may be used to, primarily from Russia, 
for example, but not only that.

00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:44.110
It is often a matter of weakening that trust in the institutions,
 of what is true and of undermining democracy
 or a democratic establishment.

00:07:44.150 --> 00:07:49.640
In reality, however, China has slightly different
 reasons for its disinformation campaigns and what it does.

00:07:49.840 --> 00:08:01.680
And that is, technical and scientific espionage
 and also the ambition to be the scientific, technological
 and business leader in the world.

00:08:01.880 --> 00:08:09.110
To do this, of course, 
it needs the most positive image possible,
 for people to believe it, to like it.

00:08:09.310 --> 00:08:15.800
to want to make business deals with it,
 to want to sell it something or buy something.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:23.880
It is not just about ideology, 
but also about good old money.

00:08:24.080 --> 00:08:36.490
That's why China's trying to get into that position of savior,
 and that's how I get to your question 
about if China was successful.

00:08:36.690 --> 00:08:41.410
Of course, we do not have data from
 all countries, whether global or European yet.

00:08:41.610 --> 00:08:51.200
However, where China began its largest
 disinformation campaigns in Italy,
 we have data and China was succesful.

00:08:51.400 --> 00:08:56.240
Chinese so-called Mask diplomacy,
 as it is now called, has caused it.

00:08:56.440 --> 00:09:03.180
China actually supplied protective equipment
 and similar things to Italy for free

00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:11.680
and spread information there about how China is helping 
and how the virus doesn't come from there at all.

00:09:11.880 --> 00:09:21.070
It caused that before the Mask diplomacy
about 10% of Italians had somehow
  a positive attitude or opinion of China,

00:09:21.150 --> 00:09:29.200
now it's 52% this is an extreme increase
 and at the same time 
we have evidence of how much it was disinformations.

00:09:29.400 --> 00:09:35.000
On Twitter, for example, it was very interesting
 to watch which hashtags were followed.

00:09:35.100 --> 00:09:47.490
Hashtags #GsoChinaandItaly and #forzaCinaeItalia, 
over 46% of posts were created by automatic bots and not real people.

00:09:47.690 --> 00:09:52.930
even so, it had such a big impact 
about a 42% increase in chinese popularity.

00:09:53.130 --> 00:09:55.040
We can say that at least 
somewhere China was successful.

00:09:55.240 --> 00:10:00.000
China knows how to use propaganda
 and misinformation,

00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:08.600
unfortunately because it has had many years of testing at home, 
so we need to focus more on it and learn to fight it.

00:10:09.801 --> 00:10:13.350
Alžběta Bajerová, 
you also work as an analyst at NATO in Brussel

00:10:13.550 --> 00:10:17.000
and also as an analyst,
 the Association for International Affairs

00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:21.010
from what Markéta Gregorová talked about,

00:10:21.210 --> 00:10:28.640
could it be deduced that the spread of disinformation
 and disinformation narratives by a power such as China

00:10:28.840 --> 00:10:34.300
poses a certain security threat,
 and within the geopolitics of the transatlantic region.

00:10:34.500 --> 00:10:43.480
Do you perceive that threat? 
Are they successful in threatening in Transaltantic region
 by spreading disinformations and disinformational narratives?

00:10:43.680 --> 00:10:47.240
Thank you  for the question and for the invitation.

00:10:47.440 --> 00:10:53.490
Certainly, information operations by state actors
 pose a threat to transatlantic security.

00:10:53.690 --> 00:10:58.000
And I think we saw it best right now 
with the covid-19 pandemic.

00:10:58.100 --> 00:11:05.610
At the same time, an infodemia arose 
that prevented to states from making an effective
 response to what was happening.

00:11:05.810 --> 00:11:13.530
We must say that those crises, such as the pandemic,
 are a breeding ground for all disinformation

00:11:13.730 --> 00:11:20.000
when people's attention to covid news
 was extremely high,

00:11:20.200 --> 00:11:27.500
and especially in the first wave, 
the demand for information exceeded the supply
 that official sources could provide.

00:11:27.700 --> 00:11:31.000
So people often turned to alternative sources.

00:11:31.200 --> 00:11:35.000
This is something we will probably
 see with each subsequent crisis.

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:42.400
The actors of those information operations
 took advantage of this and did not produce
 a large number of disinformation articles,

00:11:42.500 --> 00:11:48.500
but all that disinformation infrastructure
 was straining to cover just covid- 19.

00:11:48.700 --> 00:11:58.400
And these actors used covid as a carrier
 of what Mr Kalenský and Mrs Gregorová
 have already mentioned here.

00:11:58.600 --> 00:12:02.400
So that they can deliver this traditional 
light motive of all information operations.

00:12:02.600 --> 00:12:07.340
That the institutions, the media 
and our democracy cannot be trusted.

00:12:07.540 --> 00:12:11.000
But it must be said 
that the responsibility for that infodemic,

00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:14.700
massive spread of disinformation, 
among the masses and into the mainstream,

00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:18.240
we can't just blame those information operations.

00:12:18.440 --> 00:12:21.000
The biggest spreads 
of disinformation during the covid period,

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:26.000
as now confirmed by independent research
 from Harvard, Oxford and Kings College,

00:12:26.100 --> 00:12:29.560
were domestic politicians and the mainstream media.

00:12:29.760 --> 00:12:39.080
Politicians in the pandemic often relied on disinformation
 when they were in line with their political views.

00:12:39.280 --> 00:12:45.800
And after the mainstream media had to communicate
 what they were saying so they spread the disinformation.

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:52.820
And here I want to follow up on what Mrs Gregorova
 said about the spread of misinformation in Italy.

00:12:53.020 --> 00:13:01.900
Where researchers from Merck said 
that the botnets on Twiter did not have 
the greatest influence on the Italian public

00:13:02.100 --> 00:13:07.680
but the politicians themselves, 
who promoted the disinformation flowing from China,

00:13:07.880 --> 00:13:15.360
because they joined China in the Belt 
and Trails initiative last year,
 so they've been helping a lot now,

00:13:15.560 --> 00:13:20.810
that China is sending some aid 
and they have inflated how China is helping.

00:13:21.010 --> 00:13:26.320
At the same time, the media had to inform
 about what politicians are saying.

00:13:26.520 --> 00:13:32.000
At the same time, it focused a little on aid
 from China and Russia, it was exotic

00:13:32.100 --> 00:13:36.000
and it was a bigger topic than aid coming from the EU.

00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:39.000
To the statistics quoted here,
 I would just add that, at the same time,

00:13:39.200 --> 00:13:48.250
70% of Italians feel that the EU has failed
 to help Italy and respond to the corona virus.

00:13:48.450 --> 00:13:54.000
Which is an even more important number.

00:13:54.200 --> 00:14:00.100
So to sum it up, the most dangerous
 is the convergence between

00:14:00.300 --> 00:14:05.000
the disinformation infrastructure
 and the mainstream, politicians or the media.

00:14:05.200 --> 00:14:10.200
Here I would turn to Zdeněk Strnad
 as a long-time journalist and now chief editor,

00:14:10.400 --> 00:14:18.420
Mr Strnad, do you feel to some extent responsible
 for refuting disinformation as a journalist in the relevant medium?

00:14:18.620 --> 00:14:28.240
In your opinion,
 should the traditional mainstream media
 refute the disinformation, or is it someone else's job?

00:14:28.440 --> 00:14:33.000
And another thing you wrote,
 among other things, if I remember correctly

00:14:33.200 --> 00:14:40.110
an article mentioning that disinformations 
and fake new news are nuclear weapons of the 21st century.

00:14:40.310 --> 00:14:42.750
Can you explain what did you mean?

00:14:45.500 --> 00:14:50.480
First to the second question

00:14:50.680 --> 00:14:54.825
the article I wrote
 in which it was written that disinformation

00:14:55.025 --> 00:14:59.999
is the nuclear weapons of the 21st century
 is based on a simple premise

00:15:00.290 --> 00:15:09.770
The purpose of  every war
 or conquest of a territory

00:15:09.970 --> 00:15:14.240
is actually to obtain resources
 which are in that territory.

00:15:14.440 --> 00:15:19.279
whether they are natural resources, 
people, whatever

00:15:19.479 --> 00:15:23.999
If you fight for a territory
 by traditional methods,

00:15:23.929 --> 00:15:31.719
the ground war or so,
 then there is some damage in that territory.

00:15:32.207 --> 00:15:35.999
There is  damaged infrastructure
 or casualties and so on.

00:15:36.213 --> 00:15:38.783
but when using disinformation as such,

00:15:39.055 --> 00:15:41.965
So if you are doing it very intelligently

00:15:42.584 --> 00:15:49.204
and given the budgets of those states
 we are talking about,

00:15:49.404 --> 00:15:52.064
devoted to spreading disinformations

00:15:52.264 --> 00:15:57.400
and  colleague mentioned here,

00:15:57.223 --> 00:16:00.000
for example, the influence of China, 
here in the Czech Republic,

00:16:01.019 --> 00:16:06.300
So given how much money goes
 into those disinformation campaigns

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:12.216
and how, as has already been said here,
 with those subjects

00:16:11.059 --> 00:16:15.449
that are now beginning to
 spread disinformation and financing it,

00:16:15.649 --> 00:16:18.188
trying to gain influence as in that territory,

00:16:18.388 --> 00:16:25.330
so it is quite obvious that when you use that disinformations

00:16:25.530 --> 00:16:30.576
so the influence and access to resources you can get

00:16:30.776 --> 00:16:36.046
without damaging things you dont want to damage.

00:16:36.246 --> 00:16:40.800
and now I would like to ask on the first question,
 how exactly was it?

00:16:41.600 --> 00:16:43.770
Because other speakers mentioned

00:16:43.790 --> 00:16:49.420
that the medias are to some extent
 responsible for refuting the misinformation.

00:16:51.620 --> 00:16:58.000
It is very difficult especially 
when we take into account the situation

00:16:58.001 --> 00:17:03.450
that arose from the beginning of the year 
due to the covid pandemic.

00:17:03.650 --> 00:17:07.030
There was a huge social isolation of some groups,

00:17:07.230 --> 00:17:10.635
and I was working a lot with seniorsat the time.

00:17:10.835 --> 00:17:14.100
There the problem was absolutely the most striking.

00:17:14.300 --> 00:17:23.000
Dozens of chain mails circulate in these closed groups,

00:17:23.200 --> 00:17:26.000
in which the information 
spreads completely uncontrollably

00:17:26.200 --> 00:17:32.390
unlike social networks, which are used  
by other groups of the population,

00:17:32.301 --> 00:17:35.921
but there is actually almost no public control.

00:17:35.007 --> 00:17:43.727
and it is important to realize for what purpouse
 or which are credible sources of informations.

00:17:44.073 --> 00:17:48.793
Each of those groups has some sources, 
this has chain emails.

00:17:49.074 --> 00:17:55.900
Some simply follow certain websites, 
certain groups on social networks and so on.

00:17:56.168 --> 00:18:01.000
and the information circulates in these closed 
groups or in those channels and circles.

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:09.800
However, there is one channel that everyone, 
no matter how his credibility is questioned,

00:18:09.606 --> 00:18:16.200
it still has enormous credibility in the eyes of the public,
 of all the public, of all age groups,,

00:18:16.400 --> 00:18:18.942
and these are the public medias.

00:18:17.855 --> 00:18:25.000
which, as I said, despite all the criticism,
 still have enormous credibility,

00:18:24.910 --> 00:18:31.270
so I think that their role in today's world

00:18:31.470 --> 00:18:34.200
and the current information situation 
and completely irreplaceable.

00:18:34.095 --> 00:18:40.999
I personally I think their importance
 is also the reason why such a war is waged against them.

00:18:41.199 --> 00:18:44.200
The very last thing I get is 
to what you asked first.

00:18:44.400 --> 00:18:46.600
if I feel responsible for it as chief editor.

00:18:46.800 --> 00:18:50.999
Of course, I feel responsible within our readers and

00:18:51.020 --> 00:18:54.400
I think that this is the task not only 
of the chief editors of the local medias,

00:18:54.600 --> 00:18:55.648
and people who work there

00:18:55.848 --> 00:19:01.011
but actually all people who simply 
work in public space in any way.

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:04.500
or even among your friends,
 among the family actually

00:19:04.700 --> 00:19:11.300
everyone should be responsible for that within
 those people who can simply influences.

00:19:11.301 --> 00:19:17.000
Due to the fact that
 I am the chief editor of a magazine

00:19:17.100 --> 00:19:22.500
that reads a number of people, 
so I definitely feel the responsibility

00:19:22.700 --> 00:19:26.600
I feel a responsibility
 for this within us and honestly

00:19:26.800 --> 00:19:33.900
I'm a little ashamed when it is taken 
as  journalism, or journalist to journalism as whole

00:19:34.100 --> 00:19:37.700
because what some colleagues produce

00:19:37.705 --> 00:19:43.300
it is sometimes hair-raising.

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:51.756
And the last thing I think there is a completely
 significant and huge influence of the family.

00:19:51.956 --> 00:19:58.500
Because children who are, let's say,
 far more sensitive to those fake news

00:19:58.700 --> 00:20:03.034
or let's say children and teenagers
 just as we say young people.

00:20:03.234 --> 00:20:09.474
At least from my point of view, 
as well as adults who perceive some media as authorities,

00:20:09.711 --> 00:20:15.061
in my case the public medias, so I think
 that those teenagers and children

00:20:15.261 --> 00:20:20.000
there is influence of a family, 
which up to a certain age

00:20:20.200 --> 00:20:22.100
considers a completely irreplaceable authority.

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:24.630
Probably thats all for the beginning, thank you.

00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:27.000
So I will follow up and address Jakub Kalenský,

00:20:27.200 --> 00:20:31.500
Mr. Kalenský, you talked about influential 
operations and disinformations

00:20:31.700 --> 00:20:33.700
and their impact on society in the US Congress,

00:20:33.800 --> 00:20:38.573
and you are trying to make 
the Euro-Atlantic area a better response to

00:20:38.773 --> 00:20:43.300
disinformation and its impact on our society.

00:20:44.500 --> 00:20:46.130
The question is simple.

00:20:46.330 --> 00:20:52.800
How do you think society, politicians or media
 should fight againts disinformations?

00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:55.500
What is the way to fight them?

00:20:55.700 --> 00:21:00.760
First of all, it is necessary to accept
 that it will be a more options

00:21:00.960 --> 00:21:03.700
and not that it will simply be the right option.

00:21:03.900 --> 00:21:07.700
Sometimes you hear different people
 in that information space

00:21:07.900 --> 00:21:10.940
saying that one thing will solve everything.

00:21:11.140 --> 00:21:16.330
Either we would have to accept
 that this one solution is simply not enough

00:21:16.530 --> 00:21:26.000
or we would aim for a higher level of media literacy
 than is still available to humanity in 2020

00:21:26.200 --> 00:21:33.030
It seems to me more rational the first possibility 
that we need a larger range of those solutions,

00:21:33.230 --> 00:21:34.740
not just one solution.

00:21:34.940 --> 00:21:42.000
And that we finally need to do more 
and think less about if we are doing something

00:21:41.902 --> 00:21:47.402
One thing we really should learn 
from those Russians and Chinese

00:21:47.602 --> 00:21:52.800
they're not afraid to make mistakes. 
They are just acting

00:21:53.000 --> 00:22:04.200
and are not afraid to use a relatively primitive
 but centuries-tested method of trial and error.

00:22:04.400 --> 00:22:08.500
They are just trying to spread the information.

00:22:08.700 --> 00:22:12.500
The channels and the messages 
that work for them are repeated,

00:22:12.687 --> 00:22:15.200
nd if something doesn't work for them,
 they look away from it.

00:22:15.400 --> 00:22:21.400
On the contrary, since 2015, the European Union
 has produced 70 different documents

00:22:21.600 --> 00:22:23.800
on the topic of how to deal with disinformations

00:22:24.000 --> 00:22:28.000
Basically, we're still looking for the perfect 
solution instead of finally doing something.

00:22:28.200 --> 00:22:32.530
There are only a few individuals
 from the European institutions,

00:22:32.730 --> 00:22:37.620
who works every day instead of thinking
 about what would be good to do

00:22:37.820 --> 00:22:44.660
I don't know what it's entirely that maybe 
it's because those information Aggressors

00:22:44.860 --> 00:22:50.900
have a little more such morality 
or adaptive thinking

00:22:51.100 --> 00:22:56.800
towards conflict situation while we'd still
 like to pretend that there is no conflict

00:22:57.000 --> 00:22:59.999
and that we can talk from it.

00:23:00.199 --> 00:23:08.219
The moment we turn these two fundamental obstacles
 that prevent us from reacting to it effectively,

00:23:08.419 --> 00:23:13.100
or reconciling with the fact that different
 audiences need different solutions

00:23:13.300 --> 00:23:16.970
and reconciling with 
the need to do more, talk less

00:23:17.170 --> 00:23:19.800
and that we have to come to terms with it.
 that  we will make mistakes.

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:24.620
So then we have great opportunities
 to do everything

00:23:26.820 --> 00:23:33.950
I have been trying for some time to talk about 
such four basic lines of defense against disinformation.

00:23:36.150 --> 00:23:37.400
The first one is completely primitive

00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:39.000
We  need to more document,

00:23:39.200 --> 00:23:45.340
our big problem is that 
we still don't have a complete picture.

00:23:45.540 --> 00:23:49.230
We still do not know
 how many disinformations information aggressors

00:23:49.430 --> 00:23:51.500
are spreading every day and how successful they are.

00:23:51.700 --> 00:23:55.400
The honorable Member has spoken
 about the opinion poll in Italy.

00:23:55.600 --> 00:24:00.400
We would need opinion polls
 that measure the success of disinformation

00:24:00.600 --> 00:24:07.990
every quarter of the year for all 27 Member States
 or ideal for the whole of Europe.

00:24:08.190 --> 00:24:13.360
But if you asked me, who spends 
60 to 80 hours a week with this problem,

00:24:13.632 --> 00:24:18.999
how many people in the Czech Republic
 believe that Skripal poisoned himself

00:24:19.199 --> 00:24:23.389
or that MH17 was shot down by Ukrainians,
 I won't tell you. I dont know.

00:24:23.589 --> 00:24:26.300
And that's the problem that we don't even
 know  the exact extent of the problem,

00:24:26.500 --> 00:24:29.153
but then we are badly creating solutions.

00:24:29.353 --> 00:24:34.500
The 2nd line of defense is raising 
awareness of what the threat is.

00:24:34.700 --> 00:24:41.800
Mr. Strnad talked about the fact that 
medias can inform more  and I think they can

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:46.600
I'm  glad that some media
 do it in the Czech Republic,

00:24:46.800 --> 00:24:51.770
I think maybe Denik N, RespeKt or Aktuálně,

00:24:51.970 --> 00:24:56.051
they quite try to do it on a regular basis
 which is great.

00:24:56.251 --> 00:25:00.161
I have even noticed the Eurozpravy 
that it is trying.

00:25:00.162 --> 00:25:01.700
That's great and I'm glad that some media do,

00:25:01.701 --> 00:25:03.600
but on the other side, 
it would certainly be possible to do it more.

00:25:03.800 --> 00:25:07.120
We can't think that only media will solve this.

00:25:07.320 --> 00:25:12.690
I'll talk about what Mr. Strand said,
 we just have the problem,

00:25:12.890 --> 00:25:13.800
again, disinformators know it,

00:25:14.400 --> 00:25:16.999
Different audiences 
receive information differently.

00:25:17.199 --> 00:25:22.200
We have to count with the fact
 that some Mr. Balda

00:25:22.222 --> 00:25:26.660
somewhere near Bruntál 
simply will not consume Aktuálně or Respekt.

00:25:26.860 --> 00:25:30.030
We have to find the channel
 that speaks to him,

00:25:30.230 --> 00:25:35.830
and again these disinformers can do much better 
than we can. Just by trial and error.

00:25:36.030 --> 00:25:42.850
They don't really hesitate to open offices 
in all the Scandinavian countries

00:25:43.050 --> 00:25:47.600
and close them in a month
 because it doesn't work.

00:25:47.800 --> 00:25:54.600
Because Finns do not need to read in bad Finnish written
 what is happening in Ukraine.

00:25:54.800 --> 00:25:57.780
So they are trying some different channels.

00:25:57.980 --> 00:26:05.061
The third line of defense and
 the correction of our weaknesses, such as media literacy,

00:26:05.261 --> 00:26:08.231
and it is related to those social networks

00:26:08.431 --> 00:26:10.501
I don't consider them to be bad guys, on the other hand,

00:26:10.701 --> 00:26:15.721
they could do a lot more so 
that the disinformations don't spread there.

00:26:15.921 --> 00:26:23.464
The fact that YouTube is able to recommend
  to viewers in recommended videos Russia Today,

00:26:23.664 --> 00:26:28.900
it's just as if Tesco offered you heroin
 at the cash register.

00:26:29.100 --> 00:26:32.060
I just dont get it, how is this possible.

00:26:32.438 --> 00:26:35.800
And the 4th line of defense and 
that's something we do very little,

00:26:36.000 --> 00:26:45.000
And it's a thing where I'm slightly happy 
that it was written into the European democracy action plan.

00:26:45.200 --> 00:26:47.250
We must punish those information aggressors,

00:26:47.450 --> 00:26:51.830
and we can't just tell the victims of information
 aggression, prepare better next time.

00:26:52.030 --> 00:26:58.570
We don't deal with crimes like this,
 we don't tell Breivik victims, you should have run faster

00:26:58.770 --> 00:27:00.000
and you should have bought better armor.

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:03.900
No, we're trying to arrest that Breivik 
so he doesn't shoot people anymore.

00:27:04.100 --> 00:27:08.580
But since 2015, we have done nothing
 at all to nor Russia nor China,

00:27:08.780 --> 00:27:13.900
and for their information operations
 to bear some unwanted costs.

00:27:14.100 --> 00:27:17.555
Until we change the mindset here,
 they will continue.

00:27:17.755 --> 00:27:20.565
And as long as they continue to do so,
 they will have results, so the 4th line,

00:27:20.765 --> 00:27:27.135
I would probably say
 that it will be the most important there.

00:27:27.335 --> 00:27:33.900
If we don't do it then all three of the previous lines
 may just be wasted.

00:27:35.100 --> 00:27:37.770
I thank you, Let me just specify
 that just yesterday

00:27:37.970 --> 00:27:42.000
the European Commission issued 
the so-called Democracy action plan

00:27:42.200 --> 00:27:46.200
and there is proposition as one of the possible
 solutions to combat disinformation

00:27:46.400 --> 00:27:48.000
the possibility of imposing sanctions on subjects

00:27:48.200 --> 00:27:52.380
who purposefully and systematically
 spread such disinformation

00:27:52.580 --> 00:27:56.700
so it is such a new thing that may be
 transformed into a legislative act

