your questions will be answered, so dont be afraid
 to ask questions in the chat.

00:28:16.080 --> 00:28:18.700
I would like to ask Marketa Gregorová,

00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:26.070
Mr Kalenský talked
 about the influence of disinformation.

00:28:26.270 --> 00:28:28.000
I will specifically 
ask about political influence,

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:32.400
because you are a Member of the European Parliament
 sitting in the Legislature of the European Union,

00:28:32.600 --> 00:28:36.900
how do you actually feel that political influence
 there through disinformation campaigns?

00:28:37.100 --> 00:28:44.710
Whether its the views of your colleagues
 from other factions or the amendments they put forward,

00:28:44.910 --> 00:28:47.500
how do they feel about the various
 legislative proposals of the commission

00:28:47.700 --> 00:28:49.500
do you feel the influence 
and results of disinformations?

00:28:50.700 --> 00:28:54.200
So I will,  
although I am here in the European Parliament

00:28:54.400 --> 00:28:56.500
to start a little bit from the Czech level,

00:28:56.700 --> 00:29:01.000
because I think that we 
and everyone here actually see the influence

00:29:01.200 --> 00:29:03.000
and even more the political one,

00:29:03.200 --> 00:29:07.660
because we have witnessed demonstrations  in Prague.

00:29:07.860 --> 00:29:14.320
Here we have seen how you can start
 a wave of solidarity at the beginning of a pandemic

00:29:14.588 --> 00:29:17.600
when everyone sews maks 
and is encouraging others to handle it,

00:29:17.800 --> 00:29:20.401
and when the 2nd wave came,

00:29:20.601 --> 00:29:24.000
of course, not only through disinformation 
and government´s behavior,

00:29:24.200 --> 00:29:30.300
but also due to disinformations regarding the
 effectiveness of those protective equipment

00:29:30.500 --> 00:29:32.000
or the danger of the virus,

00:29:32.200 --> 00:29:37.480
and suddenly solidarity
 and sewing maks becomes resistance.

00:29:38.700 --> 00:29:42.800
Not believing to the government
 or other experts saying.

00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:46.300
and of course the political impact
 of the demonstrations.

00:29:47.588 --> 00:29:53.588
Which now may seemed like only
 a part of society feels it that way,

00:29:53.788 --> 00:30:00.000
in my opinion, this will be reflected especially
 in the elections next year, to the parliament,

00:30:00.119 --> 00:30:01.919
and true impact comes out.

00:30:02.119 --> 00:30:11.859
The European level is something
 little different because what the EU

00:30:12.059 --> 00:30:17.979
can do and has autority during through pandemic,
 was mainly some cross-border cooperation

00:30:18.179 --> 00:30:22.339
and coordination of the transport of 
protective equipment or other materials.

00:30:22.539 --> 00:30:26.800
Then, of course, financial aid 
 and there I must say that from the beginning

00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:29.600
there was a relatively large solidarity

00:30:29.800 --> 00:30:35.000
and a relatively large effort to obtain
 as many funds as possible

00:30:35.200 --> 00:30:40.171
for those funds of economic recovery
 but also for the purchase of protective equipment

00:30:40.371 --> 00:30:42.637
to countries where second wave hits harder.

00:30:42.839 --> 00:30:45.500
And after all, we as the Czech Republic also felt it,

00:30:45.700 --> 00:30:50.200
when, I think lung ventilators,
 we were provided with this fund.

00:30:51.193 --> 00:30:58.999
So I would say that I did not see the political effects
 so much that the solidarity persisted there,

00:30:59.199 --> 00:31:01.469
but I think that each individual member state,

00:31:01.669 --> 00:31:06.800
not just the Czech Republic,
 felt the political effects individually.

00:31:06.590 --> 00:31:11.200
And it can also have very long-term 
and long-lasting consequences

00:31:11.400 --> 00:31:16.260
and the way how our democracy will remain strong.

00:31:18.460 --> 00:31:20.537
Thank you, now I would like to
 turn to Alžběta Bajerová.

00:31:21.737 --> 00:31:26.800
Regarding disinformation during a pandemic, 
which is the main topic of this panel

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:31.000
that are definitely related health risks

00:31:31.200 --> 00:31:34.800
because if we spread disinformation 
and narratives such as covid doesnt exist,

00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:38.400
don´t wear masks and so on.
 It ceirtanly has health effects

00:31:38.600 --> 00:31:40.750
and health risks can also be life threatening

00:31:40.950 --> 00:31:46.400
You, as an analyst for
 the Public Affairs Association and NATO

00:31:46.600 --> 00:31:53.030
do you see these health risks, 
and is there really any evidence

00:31:53.230 --> 00:31:58.840
that disinformation does have an impact
 in this area of health and

00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:01.610
affects human lives and human health?

00:32:01.810 --> 00:32:03.000
Thanks for the question

00:32:03.200 --> 00:32:08.900
complex data and some clear statistics 
and does not yet exist,

00:32:08.877 --> 00:32:14.900
but I think we can see the primary 
and secondary health effects.

00:32:15.100 --> 00:32:20.600
The direct effects are, for example, 
when 700 Iranians died of methanol poisoning,

00:32:20.800 --> 00:32:27.700
after trying to distill the alcohol
 that was said to be able to cure covid.

00:32:27.900 --> 00:32:32.500
It is an example of some 
disinformation about treatment,

00:32:32.700 --> 00:32:38.700
sounding seemingly innocent, 
can result in the deaths of 700 people.

00:32:38.900 --> 00:32:45.400
Another direct effect will certainly be
 the disinformation regarding vaccinations for covid,

00:32:45.600 --> 00:32:47.290
which is already growing.

00:32:47.490 --> 00:32:50.000
I think that the moment vaccinations start,

00:32:50.200 --> 00:32:52.250
we will definitely see 
a second wave of disinformation,

00:32:52.450 --> 00:32:58.800
when people will unnecessarily die
 because they refuse to be vaccinated.

00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:04.467
Secondary effects then are 
when people do not follow the measures

00:33:04.667 --> 00:33:09.227
because they do not believe in covid,
 and this causes next spreading.

00:33:09.427 --> 00:33:14.800
Which then has the cumulative effect 
when hospitals are full and so on.

00:33:15.000 --> 00:33:20.800
The direct effect of disinformations 
can be extremely harmful,

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:22.800
we can also see it outside healthcare.

00:33:23.000 --> 00:33:26.600
For example in the USA an armed man
 broke into a restaurant in 2017,

00:33:26.800 --> 00:33:33.999
because he firmly believed that the Clinton family
 kept there and abused small children.

00:33:34.199 --> 00:33:41.241
In the UK, dozens of 5G towers
 have been destroyed by people,

00:33:41.441 --> 00:33:43.711
who believed the 5G is harmful.

00:33:43.911 --> 00:33:48.751
According to the survey, 
only a small percentage of people in the UK

00:33:48.752 --> 00:33:51.900
trust alternative media, compared to the US.

00:33:52.100 --> 00:33:54.500
But this small percentage is enough

00:33:54.700 --> 00:33:59.140
for the effect of disinformation
 to be really harmful.

00:33:59.340 --> 00:34:03.000
The potential threat to
 those information operations

00:34:03.200 --> 00:34:10.300
is, that those groups of people who are so 
deeply convinced of this disinformation

00:34:10.500 --> 00:34:12.710
can be weaponized from a distance.

00:34:12.595 --> 00:34:14.700
Weaponize by targeted disinformations.

00:34:14.633 --> 00:34:19.103
for example, for destroying
 the critical information infrastructure,

00:34:20.534 --> 00:34:23.600
and something like this could be used,
 for example, in conflict.

