that our dependence on social networks

00:35:09.900 --> 00:35:16.200
is actually one of the consequences of
 an addiction and creating of social bubbles

00:35:16.400 --> 00:35:18.210
that are just impermeable?

00:35:18.294 --> 00:35:21.600
And do you think 
that if we disconnect us more from the Internet

00:35:21.800 --> 00:35:28.500
would the bubbles start to burst a little 
or do you have a different opinion?

00:35:28.700 --> 00:35:34.400
You are saying "disconnecting from the Internet",

00:35:36.400 --> 00:35:43.900
so to me, frankly,  it's like a situation
 that I don't even consider,

00:35:44.100 --> 00:35:47.000
because disconnecting 
from the Internet is something, in my opinion,

00:35:47.200 --> 00:35:48.900
like inventing Time Machine.

00:35:49.100 --> 00:35:54.830
The campaing Day Offline, 
you were talking about was not just about

00:35:55.030 --> 00:35:58.999
disconnecting people completely, but first

00:35:58.979 --> 00:36:03.489
tried to balance
 their approach to social networks.

00:36:03.689 --> 00:36:06.000
in order not to live only in the closure
 in those one bubbles,

00:36:06.100 --> 00:36:10.770
on the contrary,
 to get out of those bubbles, they drew information

00:36:10.970 --> 00:36:14.500
also from other sources 
because returning to those social bubbles,

00:36:14.700 --> 00:36:20.500
is basically certain regardless
 of those social bubbles

00:36:20.460 --> 00:36:26.700
arise arise on the internet 
or whether they arise simply in real life

00:36:26.900 --> 00:36:32.940
because before the influence of the internet,

00:36:34.281 --> 00:36:37.800
when noone was Facebook or elsewhere,

00:36:38.000 --> 00:36:40.500
was going to work, to pub and had family.

00:36:40.624 --> 00:36:44.200
Those were three social bubbles at that time.

00:36:44.400 --> 00:36:47.117
But how to get out of this, 
I would like to mention one more campaing.

00:36:47.317 --> 00:36:52.300
In this year's coronavirus period,

00:36:52.500 --> 00:37:03.248
we actually started a show, on one 
regional television, called Prague for Seniors.

00:37:03.448 --> 00:37:11.047
one of the goals was to spread information
 among one of the most endangered groups,

00:37:11.247 --> 00:37:13.517
which in this case were seniors.

00:37:13.717 --> 00:37:17.957
Who, as I say, do not believe
 what is in the official media,

00:37:18.157 --> 00:37:22.396
chain emails with  an incredible amount of
 disinformation are shared among them,

00:37:22.596 --> 00:37:24.297
There is no control in that.

00:37:24.567 --> 00:37:36.527
How you convince any social group 
that you want to tell them something?

00:37:36.629 --> 00:37:40.300
And they should give some importance on it.

00:37:40.500 --> 00:37:44.100
Well, you have to interpret it in a way
 that they believe,

00:37:44.300 --> 00:37:48.200
and because one of the biggest 
arguments that speaks

00:37:48.400 --> 00:37:52.800
for the truth of certain information 
is when someone you trust tells you.

00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:56.559
So we were thinking about 
who these people would trust,

00:37:56.908 --> 00:38:00.000
who is the one, who enters their bubble

00:38:00.200 --> 00:38:03.999
and at the same time is important for them.

00:38:04.199 --> 00:38:10.100
So after a long deliberation
 we chose a moderator named Saša Hemala,

00:38:12.300 --> 00:38:17.000
Everyone from this group knows him.

00:38:19.200 --> 00:38:21.708
He was announcing news and informations

00:38:21.908 --> 00:38:26.500
about what it looks in Prague
 with current supplies.

00:38:26.700 --> 00:38:30.000
It was a show that ran three times a week,
 had a relatively high audience.

00:38:30.800 --> 00:38:33.600
And when Mr Kalenský spoke about

00:38:33.800 --> 00:38:36.800
how this should be reflected in the media.

00:38:37.000 --> 00:38:41.190
This is one of the ways in which the media,

00:38:41.390 --> 00:38:49.010
regardless of their size and reach,
 could fight it.

00:38:49.555 --> 00:38:56.800
Think about the need and specifics of people,
 who you are talking to,

00:38:57.000 --> 00:39:08.310
think who is the person 
who will speak to them through your medium.

00:39:08.510 --> 00:39:10.659
learn to speak their language,

00:39:10.663 --> 00:39:13.363
thats's incredibly important.

00:39:13.563 --> 00:39:17.103
then you have some chance

00:39:17.303 --> 00:39:22.800
that you will somehow slow down
 the crazy flow of disinformation.

00:39:23.000 --> 00:39:24.500
if not stop it.

00:39:24.700 --> 00:39:28.800
It's hard job, there is no universal recipe for it,

00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:32.050
just the personal responsibility of everyone,

00:39:32.250 --> 00:39:35.100
whether it's a parent,

00:39:35.286 --> 00:39:39.100
or it's a person who has the opportunity to
 influence the content of a media,

00:39:39.300 --> 00:39:40.350
or whether it's an ordinary citizen.

00:39:40.550 --> 00:39:42.500
I think the principle is the same

00:39:42.481 --> 00:39:44.741
maybe just like that the degree 
of responsibility is various,

00:39:44.774 --> 00:39:46.300
depending on how many people you influence.

00:39:46.169 --> 00:39:50.500
Jakub Kalensky, you mentioned
 both the Democracy Action Plan

00:39:50.700 --> 00:39:54.700
but also the responsibility 
and a certain role of online platforms

00:39:54.900 --> 00:39:57.300
specifically mentioned by YouTube.

00:39:58.800 --> 00:40:01.810
Do you think that the Commission is trying,
 in the Action Plan for Democracy,

00:40:02.010 --> 00:40:08.200
to ensure that, in the future,
 online platforms would be more regulated?

00:40:08.400 --> 00:40:12.500
and they have more responsibility
 for fight againts disinformation?

00:40:12.700 --> 00:40:16.400
Do you think that this is the right way
 that there should be EU regulation

00:40:16.600 --> 00:40:21.300
that would bind online platforms like
 Facebook, Twitter or Tik Tok and so on.

00:40:22.500 --> 00:40:25.999
to really be looking for
 disinformations and deleting it?

00:40:26.199 --> 00:40:28.333
Isnt it close to censorship?

00:40:28.533 --> 00:40:30.500
Who will decide what is true and what is not?

00:40:32.702 --> 00:40:34.082
I admit that I probably don't have a completely

00:40:34.282 --> 00:40:38.502
strong opinion on regulation or non-regulation.

00:40:38.702 --> 00:40:41.900
It's not like I want to avoid an answer.

00:40:42.100 --> 00:40:43.800
It's not that I'm not knowing the topic,

00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:49.200
but I'm actually still not sure if it's a good idea
 or if it's not a good idea.

00:40:49.400 --> 00:40:54.500
It is clear that the so-called
 self-regulatory principle,

00:40:54.457 --> 00:40:58.377
which the European Commission
 chose sometime in 2016/2017,

00:41:01.892 --> 00:41:05.200
turns out to be almost useless.

00:41:05.400 --> 00:41:09.600
In its own documents, 
the commission always admits that,

00:41:09.603 --> 00:41:11.999
the platforms have shown us activities

00:41:12.199 --> 00:41:14.500
that actually do nothing about
 the spreading of disinformation

00:41:14.700 --> 00:41:18.200
and always, as every month,
 Commission threatens them,

00:41:18.400 --> 00:41:21.000
if you don't get better next time
 so we have to think about regulation.

00:41:21.200 --> 00:41:22.200
Thats being said over two years.

00:41:22.400 --> 00:41:28.600
Which seems to me to be that the level 
of solving the problem is not entirely high,

00:41:28.693 --> 00:41:31.100
but I'm not really sure.

00:41:36.301 --> 00:41:41.500
Maybe we should think about that a little 
in the style we think of the medias

00:41:41.700 --> 00:41:47.999
I think how often is there a debate about
 whether social networks are actually publishers,

00:41:50.988 --> 00:41:52.200
they are publishing information or not.

00:41:52.400 --> 00:41:54.600
I think, gradually shows that, yes, they are.

00:41:55.800 --> 00:42:00.170
I think, for example, 
the recent US election showed it a bit.

00:42:00.370 --> 00:42:04.600
while until then, Facebook 
and Twitter always washed their hands

00:42:04.800 --> 00:42:07.350
and were saying we don't really interfere
 with what is spreading in our networks

00:42:07.550 --> 00:42:12.900
and we only deal with such 
coordinated inauthentic behavior.

00:42:13.100 --> 00:42:16.200
so suddenly as soon as 
they indicated that Donald Trump

00:42:16.400 --> 00:42:19.800
was lying about winning the election
 or lying about those falsifications,

00:42:20.000 --> 00:42:26.890
so they showed us, that they care nor just 
about unauthentic behavior, but also about the factual level

00:42:26.876 --> 00:42:28.700
Which I quite like,

00:42:28.900 --> 00:42:32.700
they came up with it themselves
 without any regulation,

00:42:32.900 --> 00:42:37.969
but at the same time 
I admit that it's not certain,

00:42:38.510 --> 00:42:39.800
that the networks will do it for us.

00:42:40.000 --> 00:42:45.600
That "who will decide",
 I will admit that the question,

00:42:45.800 --> 00:42:47.600
although I have been listening
 it for several years,

00:42:47.800 --> 00:42:49.480
I don't really like it.

00:42:49.680 --> 00:42:55.200
It suddenly makes from the truth
 some personal property,

00:42:55.400 --> 00:42:59.100
and I am deeply convinced
 that there is no personal property in the truth.

00:43:00.500 --> 00:43:04.300
Old scholastic definition 
speaks of adaequatio rei et intellectus

00:43:04.500 --> 00:43:09.030
as a harmony of what you have
 in your head with what is outside.

00:43:08.306 --> 00:43:10.000
Thats a process of searching.

00:43:10.080 --> 00:43:15.530
You are searching if
 whats is happening between your ears

00:43:14.539 --> 00:43:19.000
matches what's going on outside the brain.

00:43:19.029 --> 00:43:21.999
I think that everyone
 here simply has to be an arbitrator,

00:43:22.199 --> 00:43:24.100
which should not mean,

00:43:24.300 --> 00:43:29.600
That the networks or platforms or any other
 actor will not have the responsibility.

00:43:29.800 --> 00:43:33.070
After all, the platforms can also decide,
 that they have some responsibility,

00:43:33.270 --> 00:43:34.200
and in that case of Donald Trump,

00:43:34.400 --> 00:43:37.000
they obviously said it to themselves
 and they decided.

00:43:37.200 --> 00:43:40.500
this is just something we're going to refute,

00:43:40.432 --> 00:43:43.300
and I'd even like to see them do this more often.

00:43:43.500 --> 00:43:47.300
I think that here each of us 
will have the responsibility,

00:43:47.500 --> 00:43:49.000
whether it's at the level of the individual

00:43:49.200 --> 00:43:53.600
or at the level of a huge company like Facebook.

00:43:53.800 --> 00:43:58.680
I don't mind at all
 that if they take it on their own.

00:43:58.880 --> 00:44:02.650
Of course I will be happy if they do it
 in cooperation with renowned fact checkers

00:44:02.616 --> 00:44:06.200
and non-profits who have been
 doing on this for years

00:44:06.167 --> 00:44:08.700
and its plenty of them.

00:44:08.750 --> 00:44:13.099
if they have the will it will not 
be difficult to implement,

00:44:13.213 --> 00:44:20.200
but I don't think we just have to look for
 someone outside who defines it for us

00:44:20.400 --> 00:44:23.800
instead of us so we can wash our hands
 and say we don't really decide

00:44:24.000 --> 00:44:25.330
what's true or not.

00:44:24.983 --> 00:44:26.800
We should accept the responsibility

00:44:27.000 --> 00:44:39.285
I think it's up to each individual, every medium
 to decide where the boundaries are.

00:44:39.999 --> 00:44:45.459
We can push them to have those boundaries 
where we think it is right.

00:44:45.800 --> 00:44:47.500
For example, 
as for the pandemic of the corona virus,

00:44:47.700 --> 00:44:53.500
Facebook went the way of self-regulation 
and maybe changed its algorithms

00:44:53.700 --> 00:44:57.800
and prefers messages 
that are currently issued to authorities

00:44:58.000 --> 00:45:01.310
such as the WHO. Ministry of Health and so on.

00:45:01.510 --> 00:45:03.700
This may be one way to go.

00:45:03.900 --> 00:45:07.800
I would say that in this was 
Facebook or Twitter quite successful.

00:45:08.500 --> 00:45:11.830
Markéta Gregorová regarding
 the Commission's future legislative proposals

00:45:12.030 --> 00:45:13.800
on fight againts disinformation,

00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:16.700
you will co-decide about them
 in the European Parliament.

00:45:16.900 --> 00:45:20.400
What is your point of view,
 should online platforms be legally responsible

00:45:20.419 --> 00:45:23.799
and regulated in the sense
 that they should actually search for

00:45:23.999 --> 00:45:25.289
and delete disinformation content?

00:45:25.489 --> 00:45:29.269
Or the Union and the Member States
 should go the way,

00:45:29.469 --> 00:45:32.500
as Mr Kalenský said, of analyses,

00:45:32.700 --> 00:45:35.800
data collection and gaining more information

00:45:35.702 --> 00:45:38.400
about how those narratives work
 and how they are spread.

00:45:38.401 --> 00:45:41.999
For example, the European Union has
 recently started operating in

00:45:42.199 --> 00:45:45.249
so-called European Digital Media Observatory (ATMO).

00:45:45.449 --> 00:45:49.800
which is about to work with both
 academics and fact checkers

00:45:49.976 --> 00:45:52.300
on the analysis of disinformation.

00:45:52.500 --> 00:45:53.600
What is the right way?

00:45:53.800 --> 00:45:56.540
Well, as Mr. Kalenský has already said,

00:45:56.740 --> 00:46:00.300
This is a million dollar question,
 but of course I must also agree with him,

00:46:00.500 --> 00:46:05.600
as he said at the beginning,
 that we must stop standing still
 and start doing something

00:46:05.800 --> 00:46:10.800
Often people are asking me, 
if we are losing the fight against disinformation

00:46:11.000 --> 00:46:14.200
and I am always replying
 that we haven't started fighting yet.

00:46:14.400 --> 00:46:16.300
We have no legislation.

00:46:16.500 --> 00:46:21.611
We don't have any proper tools 
or anything that would really push it forward.

00:46:21.811 --> 00:46:25.600
Anyway, to what is the best answer,

00:46:25.800 --> 00:46:28.200
it probably won't surprise anyone

00:46:28.280 --> 00:46:31.900
that I'm not completely enthusiastic 
about some self-regulation of networks,

00:46:32.100 --> 00:46:35.400
but that's because it's not a question. 
Should that be regulated?

00:46:35.429 --> 00:46:38.800
There will be regulation. 
It's about who will be responsible for it and

00:46:39.000 --> 00:46:40.800
who will be the leader of it.

00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:43.800
We are currently throwing
 that responsibility on social networks

00:46:44.000 --> 00:46:47.200
ecause we have a legal vacuum 
in this regard and no one knows.

00:46:47.400 --> 00:46:50.500
But even the networks themselves
 do not want to have that responsibility.

00:46:50.700 --> 00:46:54.600
In my opinion people think, for example, 
that Google and Facebook come to me lobbying

00:46:54.800 --> 00:46:56.200
asking to not change anything.

00:46:56.400 --> 00:46:59.700
No they are lobbying
 that they desperately want some regulation,

00:46:59.900 --> 00:47:01.500
because they are terribly unhappy about it.

00:47:01.700 --> 00:47:05.900
They are companies
 that are based on earning profit,

00:47:06.100 --> 00:47:10.470
and that is their main goal, why do they exist.

00:47:10.670 --> 00:47:13.800
It's not because they really wanted 
to make society better

00:47:14.000 --> 00:47:16.400
or more connected 
but because they make profits from it.

00:47:16.600 --> 00:47:21.800
Well, we can't really expect social
 responsibility from such companies,

00:47:22.000 --> 00:47:23.900
but the fact that they will try
 to behave in such a way

00:47:24.100 --> 00:47:28.000
that they have more and more satisfied users,
 who will bring them further profits,

00:47:28.200 --> 00:47:29.900
whether from advertising or anything else,

00:47:30.100 --> 00:47:33.240
and that is why we should not let
 them regulate themselves,

00:47:33.440 --> 00:47:37.700
because what will happen, is that they will
 only censor more and more

00:47:37.900 --> 00:47:40.600
and deal more and more what
 correct content they have there

00:47:40.800 --> 00:47:42.650
in order to have those satisfied users there,

00:47:42.850 --> 00:47:48.900
on the contrary,
 I think that governments should emancipate

00:47:49.100 --> 00:47:54.200
I prefer to be EU on our continent

00:47:54.245 --> 00:47:58.000
and, of course, governments 
and finally dive into it.

00:47:58.200 --> 00:48:00.200
Now I'm talking about the short-term approach.

00:48:00.400 --> 00:48:03.000
There is of course long-term one 
with lots of steps, media literacy or so,

00:48:03.200 --> 00:48:05.100
that I take as granted

00:48:05.300 --> 00:48:08.800
but at the same time
 and that's my last point in this.

00:48:09.000 --> 00:48:13.600
It's not that the government should
 determine some dreaded Ministry of Truth

00:48:13.800 --> 00:48:15.700
and regulate platforms.

00:48:15.877 --> 00:48:19.187
It's about the balance of who he is doing what

00:48:19.387 --> 00:48:25.950
and I think we forget that balance
 is quite beneficial in the triangle.

00:48:26.150 --> 00:48:30.400
We forget about civil society,
 the truly independent organizations

00:48:30.600 --> 00:48:34.200
and people who can control and support it.

00:48:35.800 --> 00:48:39.280
At the moment it is set up so
 that there are some organizations

00:48:39.480 --> 00:48:41.160
which are being hired by the platforms.

00:48:41.360 --> 00:48:45.650
We can trust them or we don't,
 but it is just about trust.

00:48:45.676 --> 00:48:49.662
But if is there balanced triangle

00:48:52.662 --> 00:48:55.392
and it will be supported by governments,

00:48:55.592 --> 00:48:59.400
and respected by democratic controls, 
that it is independent

00:48:59.600 --> 00:49:04.000
and the platforms will be encouraged
 to hire these agencies

00:49:04.200 --> 00:49:07.010
and they will  do fact-checking 
or checking the information

00:49:07.210 --> 00:49:10.600
and mark and show,
 not necessarily censored.

00:49:10.800 --> 00:49:12.830
Just to show, that information is not true.

00:49:13.030 --> 00:49:17.250
So I think we can get to a point
 that is neither the censorship

00:49:17.310 --> 00:49:19.500
but also not doing noything,

00:49:19.700 --> 00:49:24.200
because both are, in my opinion, 
very harmful and we must go in some direction.

00:49:24.400 --> 00:49:26.200
Thank you, since we still have 10 minutes left,

00:49:26.400 --> 00:49:32.120
I would quickly turn to the questions
 that landed in the chat,

00:49:32.320 --> 00:49:39.110
There is question which aims at Jakub Kalenský
 from Mr. Dominik Voráč

00:49:39.222 --> 00:49:44.000
"In your opinion, disinformators are winning
 because we are only thinking

00:49:44.200 --> 00:49:46.370
while disinformators are acting.

00:49:46.570 --> 00:49:49.200
but isn´t it also about that,
 that defending against disinformation

00:49:49.400 --> 00:49:54.440
is much harder and more difficult 
than creating and spreading disinformation?"

00:50:00.000 --> 00:50:01.690
Thanks for the question,

00:50:01.890 --> 00:50:04.000
because I thought we wouldn't
 get to that question,

00:50:04.200 --> 00:50:05.200
so I was answering it in the chat.

00:50:05.400 --> 00:50:07.500
So I will briefly answer here.

00:50:07.700 --> 00:50:12.300
I completely agree with the premise 
that spreading disinformation is easier

00:50:12.500 --> 00:50:13.550
than defending against them.

00:50:13.750 --> 00:50:18.550
I think that's exactly what
 we should adapt to in a situation.

00:50:18.750 --> 00:50:23.800
After all, we profess the same
 principles in the physical space

00:50:23.809 --> 00:50:25.900
as opposed to the information space.

00:50:26.100 --> 00:50:33.300
If it is easier to rob people
 than to defend against someone stealing us,

00:50:33.500 --> 00:50:38.999
so we simply set laws 
and restrictions so that it is more difficult.

00:50:40.000 --> 00:50:42.700
If it is easier to spread a toxic substance

00:50:42.900 --> 00:50:47.200
than to make sure that none of the
 inhabitants spreads any toxic substances,

00:50:47.400 --> 00:50:51.500
we simply set up such mechanisms
 so that it is more complicated.

00:50:51.700 --> 00:50:56.502
Yes, it is of course easier 
and it is up to us to solve this situation.

00:50:58.702 --> 00:51:03.800
Surely there was a time 
when there were no traffic regulations,

00:51:04.000 --> 00:51:07.000
people probably died because of it.

00:51:10.200 --> 00:51:12.460
Then someone said 
that there are too many cars

00:51:12.660 --> 00:51:17.999
so we should have some regulations
 for how we will move on those roads.

00:51:18.199 --> 00:51:22.800
Maybe we are really approaching the time
 when maybe those regulations will really be necessary.

00:51:23.000 --> 00:51:27.670
That information space has evolved to a time 
when it is already quite complicated.

00:51:27.870 --> 00:51:29.410
It's not as easy as it used to be.

00:51:29.610 --> 00:51:33.400
Governments and the big media no longer 
have a monopol on the information situation.

00:51:33.600 --> 00:51:37.000
We have new subjects here
 who don't really have the mechanisms

00:51:37.200 --> 00:51:40.121
as media or goverment have.

00:51:41.321 --> 00:51:44.121
We probably must adapt to the situation

00:51:44.321 --> 00:51:49.681
and we have to reckon with the fact
 that there are bad participants

00:51:49.881 --> 00:51:54.731
or aggressors to whom 
we simply must make it difficult

00:51:54.931 --> 00:51:59.000
and not lettim them spreading 
disinformation with impunity.

00:52:00.200 --> 00:52:03.000
We have three minutes 
so I would ask Alžběta Bajerová,

00:52:03.200 --> 00:52:06.940
she was a member of the analytical 
project ChinfluenCE

00:52:07.140 --> 00:52:11.999
within the Association for International Affairs,

00:52:12.199 --> 00:52:15.300
which is of course dealing 
with the influence of China.

00:52:15.500 --> 00:52:16.600
and thus I will follow up on Markéta,

00:52:16.800 --> 00:52:24.600
who spoke about the fact that
 China is successful in building that narrative.

00:52:24.639 --> 00:52:25.800
What do you think,

00:52:26.000 --> 00:52:32.500
is China and its hybrid threats
 and disinformations, threat for 21st century?

00:52:32.674 --> 00:52:37.794
Certainly, those state-sponsored 
information operatitions,

00:52:37.994 --> 00:52:42.144
these which are linked to China,
 they have most resources.

00:52:42.344 --> 00:52:48.800
At the same time, the information
 operations coming to Transatlantic area

00:52:49.000 --> 00:52:54.690
are not high quality. 
Mainly because language barrier

00:52:54.890 --> 00:52:57.160
and there is also a cultural barrier.

00:52:57.360 --> 00:53:03.090
The narrative that is now spreading 
and is very positive about China

00:53:03.290 --> 00:53:07.030
is quite recognizable to us, 
as Europeans, as propaganda.

00:53:07.230 --> 00:53:13.170
so I must say that so far 
the direct effectiveness is not so high,

00:53:13.089 --> 00:53:18.489
rather the risk that currently 
represents Chinese operations lies

00:53:18.689 --> 00:53:26.600
in connecting those elites on messaging of China.

00:53:26.800 --> 00:53:29.150
However, in the future, it can be assumed

00:53:29.350 --> 00:53:31.750
because of those massive resources,

00:53:31.950 --> 00:53:36.690
that the quality of operations 
resulting from East Asia will increase.

00:53:36.890 --> 00:53:39.620
So I would certainly call it a threat.

00:53:40.500 --> 00:53:42.000
Unfortunately, our time has passed,

00:53:42.200 --> 00:53:46.200
So I want to thank you for your participation
 and thank you for being here with us,

00:53:46.870 --> 00:53:47.062
even though you couldn't be here
 with us physically but at least online.

